<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>üíß Raindrop</title>

    <style>
      html {
        background: <%= Color::BACKGROUND %>;
      }
      body {
        font-size: 16pt;
        line-height: 1.5rem;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 1rem auto;
      }
      h1, h2, h3 {
        text-align: center;
        font-family: sans-serif;
      }
      header, section {
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
      }
      footer {
        font-size: 12pt;
        text-align: center;
      }
      .colors {
        font-family: monospace;
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 4px;
      }
      .colors div {
        width: 128px;
        height: 128px;
        border: 1px solid #ccc;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <header>
      <h1>Raindrop üíß</h1>
    </header>

    <section>
      <p><a href="https://github.com/kellygravelyn/raindrop">Raindrop</a> is my personal color theme I use for all of my software when I can. I use it for code editing as well as in my terminal. I made Raindrop because I wanted a light theme that felt calm and simple.</p>
      <p>A key feature of Raindrop, as far as the Sublime Text color scheme goes, is incredibly minimal use of selectors. I find that the <em>majority</em> of code is perfectly fine being rendered in a dark color on a light color. I apply colors judiciously only where I feel like it makes my experience better.</p>
      <p>Also critically I am not a designer. I don't have a background in color theory. There is probably a lot to improve here and I do over time as I experience these colors in my daily life. If you have suggestions, please feel free to <a href="https://github.com/kellygravelyn/raindrop/issues">open a GitHub issue to discuss it</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The colors üíÖüèª</h2>
      <div class="colors">
        <% Color::constants.map {|c| Color.const_get(c)}.uniq.each do |c| %>
          <div style="background: <%= c %>">
            <%= c %>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer>
      Made with ‚ô•Ô∏è by <a href="https://kellyrenee.me">Kelly Gravelyn</a>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
